-- Kan Approval Rises to 64 Percent After Cabinet Reshuffle, Sankei Reports
-- Kazuyo Sawa
-- 2010-09-20T23:24:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/kan-approval-rises-to-64-percent-after-cabinet-reshuffle-sankei-reports.html

          
          
             Japanese voter approval for Prime
Minister Naoto Kanâ€™s Cabinet rose 18 percentage points to 64
percent, according to a Sankei newspaper survey.  
 The disapproval rating dropped 19 points to 21 percent from
the last survey taken in August.  
 The ruling Democratic Party of Japan had popular support of
35 percent, up 6 points. Support for the opposition Liberal
Democratic Party dropped 1 point to 19 percent, the newspaper
said.    
 The telephone survey of 1,000 people was taken Sept. 18-19.
No margin of error was provided.  
